{"OwnerDisplayName":"Sam", "Body":"<p>Is there a measure for the rate of language drift? In one answer to <a href=\"http://english.stackexchange.com/questions/32924/is-spelling-still-drifting\">this question</a>, it was suggested that drift had slowed for technological reasons, but may also be speeding up because of different technologies.</p>\n\n<p>How is this slowing determined? I would imagine statistically?</p>\n\n<p>Is there a unit of measurement for language drift?</p>\n", "Id":"988", "LastEditorUserId":"92", "FavoriteCount":"1", "Title":"Can you measure the rate of drift?", "CreationDate":"2011-11-08T20:34:48.230", "OwnerUserId":"505", "PostTypeId":"1", "Tags":"<language-change><orthography>", "AnswerCount":"1", "comments":[], "LastEditDate":"2011-11-09T08:00:49.643", "LastEditedUser":{"UpVotes":"488", "WebsiteUrl":"http://claimid.com/louisr", "Id":"92", "AccountId":"163323", "CreationDate":"2011-09-14T02:07:23.613", "AboutMe":"<p>trying to learn and help others learn :)</p>\n", "Age":"34", "Location":"Your computer", "DownVotes":"39", "Views":"97", "Reputation":"3271", "DisplayName":"Louis Rhys", "LastAccessDate":"2014-01-18T16:45:57.423"}, "ViewCount":"236", "LastActivityDate":"2011-12-10T14:49:59.747", "Score":"6", "CommentCount":"5", "OwnerUser":{"UpVotes":"0", "WebsiteUrl":"http://sambaker.net", "Location":"United States", "Id":"505", "DownVotes":"0", "AccountId":"291720", "Views":"0", "Reputation":"131", "CreationDate":"2011-11-11T16:56:09.320", "DisplayName":"Sam", "LastAccessDate":"2011-11-20T04:32:11.460"}}